1-27-2014 Advocacy Wealth Management: As Seen In Kiplinger's Personal Finance


8-7-2014 Rob Davis Joins Advocacy Wealth Management




Tom Johnson brings a wealth of experience to the Advocacy team. His career spans more than 40 years and he has served in a variety of positions, ranging from the mailroom runner of his family’s brokerage firm in his teenage years to CEO of his own firm. Tom joined Advocacy in early 2014 from CertusSecurities, a partner of both AWM and Forge in the design of services for plaintiffs and those who wish to speak predictability in the today’s low rate and volatile market. Tom lives in Atlanta with his wife, the former Wayne Dobbs Bussey, with whom he has two children, Thomas Johnson IV and Louise.
 
Career Highlights:
 
Former Director of Johnson, Lane, Space, Smith & Co., Inc., 1984-89
 
Managed Institutional Equity Trading for Johnson, Lane™ as well as Corporate Fixed Income and Convertible Sales
 
Proprietary Trading and Arbitrage for successor firms Interstate/Johnson Lane Corp. and Wachovia Securities LLC
 
Formed Southern Trading Partners & Consultants in 1999 to serve institutional clients in convertible arbitrage strategies, as it continues to do this day
 
Formed Johnson Lane™ Advisors, LLC in 2008 to provide financial planning services to individuals and endowments
 
Formed Sage Capital Holdings, LLC in 2010 to acquire Sage Southeastern Securities, Inc.
 
Sold Sage Southeastern to CertusHoldings, Inc. in 2011 and became CEO, CCO of the renamed CertusSecurites, Inc., Member FINRA and SIPC
 
President of the Georgia Securities Association, 1986-87
 
Chairman of the Board, The Elaine Clark Center 1996-99, and 2007-2009, Vice-Chairman 2009-present
 
Dartmouth Club of Georgia, President 1985-86, Treasurer 2002-2010
 
Trustee of the Galloway School 1987-93
 
Director, Sensor Tech, Inc., a private Georgia technology company
 
Fiduciary Agent for Senior Note Holders, Lucky Litter, LLC, a pet supply company
 
Director, Fifth Market, Inc., a financial services technology company
 
BA, Dartmouth College, 1975 with Distinction in Literature and Creative Writing
 
Executive Program for Financial Planning, Terry School of Business, University of Georgia, 2008 with Distinction.
 
Registered Principal (Series 24), Registered Investment Advisor Associate (Series 65) General Securities Registered Representative (Series 7), Equity Trader (Series 55), Investment Banking (Series 79), Municipal Principal (Series 53), Interest Rate Options (Series 5), Georgia Resident Life & Health Insurance, Variable Products and Long Term Care Agent






President, COO, CCO
