Advocacy News


1-27-2014 Advocacy Wealth Management: As Seen In Kiplinger's Personal Finance


8-7-2014 Rob Davis Joins Advocacy Wealth Management




Anthony "Tony" Hosfeld joined Advocacy as one of its managing partners after working with Reliance Securities as a Vice President Financial Advisor from 2007 to 2011. While employed with Reliance, Tony worked closely with the partnership at Forge Consulting to manage the core business that would eventually evolve to become the impetus for founding Advocacy Wealth Management. Tony has worked diligently to help craft the investment platforms and principles that set Advocacy apart from other wealth management firms, creating wealth management strategies with predictable outcomes for settlement recipients.
 
Tony graduated from Wichita State University with a Bachelors of Science in Business Administration. While attending college he played football for the Shockers. After college Tony traveled internationally for General Foods for several years, negotiating several food lines into the international line of General Foods Products. Subsequently, Tony served as Senior Vice President of Ferrellgas Energy Company where he was responsible for $1 billion in annual sales along with acquisitions in the millions. After working with Ferrellgas, Tony went on to serve as a Financial Advisor for Prudential Securities until 2000. Subsequently, he began working as a Vice President Financial Advisor with Wachovia Securities until 2007, moving on to work with Reliance Securities and helping that firm launch its retail wealth management division.
 
Tony holds a number of securities licenses including the series 7, 63, 65 and variable life and health.
 
Tony currently resides in Atlanta, Georgia with his son.











