Advocacy News


1-27-2014 Advocacy Wealth Management: As Seen In Kiplinger's Personal Finance


8-7-2014 Rob Davis Joins Advocacy Wealth Management









Tim Denehy joined Advocacy Wealth Management in March 2012 as a Vice President of Trust Services. Tim works directly with injured plaintiffs and their families to provide settlement trust and special needs trust solutions as part of a comprehensive plan designed to manage and protect a lawsuit recovery.
 
With over two decades of experience in trust and financial services, Tim has worked exclusively with injured trust clients for the past ten years. Prior to joining Advocacy Wealth Management, he served in a variety of trust related positions at large banks and mid-size trust companies including as a trust consultant, trust officer, and as an estate settlement officer.
 
Tim completed the National Graduate Trust School program at Northwestern University in 1998; received his Certified Structured Settlement Consultant (CSSC) designation in 2003; and received his Certified Trust and Financial Advisor (CTFA) designation in 2007. He currently serves on the Board of Directors for the Society of Settlement Planners.
 
Tim is a graduate of the College of the Holy Cross in Worcester, Massachusetts where he earned a degree in Political Science and participated in the Navy ROTC program. He subsequently served as a Surface Warfare Officer in the United States Navy.
 
Tim currently resides in Connecticut with his wife, Barbara, and two children, Mary and Jack. Tim is the President of the Memorial Military Museum, a non-profit organization located in Bristol, Connecticut, that displays a collection of military memorabilia honoring local veterans.






President - Advocacy Trust Solutions
