Advocacy News


1-27-2014 Advocacy Wealth Management: As Seen In Kiplinger's Personal Finance


8-7-2014 Rob Davis Joins Advocacy Wealth Management






Justin has been in the investment management industry for over 14 years. He is a Chartered Financial Analyst® ("CFA”) and has attained his Series 7, 63, and 65 licenses from FINRA. Justin will be responsible for the collaborative construction of individual portfolios and ongoing monitoring both at the individual as well as the firm level for return versus risk and client profile.  According to the CFA Institute, “No credential is as widely respected in the (financial) industry for its breadth and depth of advanced and current skills, global relevance, and ethical grounding as the CFA charter. And none is harder to obtain.”
 
Prior to joining Advocacy, Justin served as a Client Portfolio Manager at Invesco where he worked on the company’s Global Equity investment team.  He has worked with individual clients as well as large institutions along with their advisers. In addition to his client portfolio management responsibilities, Justin was Director of Strategic Planning for the global firm. He is a graduate of Wake Forest University, where he earned a bachelor's in Business with a focus in finance.
 
Justin lives in Atlanta with his wife and two young daughters. He is actively involved in the local community, serving as President of the Friends of Bitsy Grant Tennis Center, a non-profit organization.
 




Chief Investment Officer
